<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 6:43PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Foard,
Wilbarger and southeastern Hardeman Counties through 715 PM CDT...
At 643 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Vernon, moving northwest at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Vernon, Lockett, Fargo, Oklaunion, Harrold, Grayback and Rayland.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
